The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) has distributed relief materials to victims of windstorms in Kabba-Bunu, Ijumu and Yagba-East local government areas of Kogi State. The disaster, which occurred last year, affected 17 communities, eight communities and one community, respectively in each of the three local government areas. The Director-General of NEMA, Mr Ahmed Habib, who was represented by Mr Justin Uwazuruonye, Head, Abuja Operations Office of the agency, disclosed this while speaking with reporters yesterday in Abuja.   Katsina targets 700,000 members in health care enrollment     Ganduje presents staff of office to Emir of Gaya     Kontagora General Hospital records 85 deliveries, 14â€¦   Uwazuruonye said the items donated to the victims included rice, beans, garri, vegetable oil, cooking condiments, mattresses, wax print, blankets, cement, nails and ceiling boards. He said the items were approved by the Federal Government through NEMA to ease the suffering of the affected people, noting that NEMA undertook the assignment on behalf of the Federal Government to distribute directly to the affected people. - Advertisement - Uwazuruonye also stated that the relief materials donated to the victims were not meant to compensate them for their belongings destroyed by the rainstorm but to cushion the effects of the incident. Representatives of the House of Representatives member representing Kabba-Ijumu Federal Constituency, Tajudeen Yusuf, the Obaro of Kabba, Obaro Otitoleke Owey, SEMA officials and other stakeholders witnessed the distribution of the items.